9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 575, L.D. 889, “An Act to Amend the
10 Laws Regarding the Department of Health and Human Services”
11 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
12 'An Act to Clarify the Release of Information by the Department of Health and
13 Human Services in the Law Regarding Automatic Referrals'
14 Amend the bill by inserting after the title and before the enacting clause the following:
15 'Emergency preamble. Whereas, acts and resolves of the Legislature do not
16 become effective until 90 days after adjournment unless enacted as emergencies; and
17 Whereas, individuals who are eligible to enroll in certain state programs will be
18 referred to other programs for which they are eligible through an automatic referral project
19 created by Public Law 2023, chapter 412; and
20 Whereas, individuals must be able to opt out of information sharing, and establishing
21 that ability requires a statutory change; and
22 Whereas, the Department of Health and Human Services and other state agencies,
23 quasi-state agencies and other entities are currently developing and implementing the
24 project, and this legislation must take effect immediately to avoid any delays; and
25 Whereas, in the judgment of the Legislature, these facts create an emergency within
26 the meaning of the Constitution of Maine and require the following legislation as
27 immediately necessary for the preservation of the public peace, health and safety; now,
28 therefore,'
29 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
30 following:
31 'Sec. 1. 22 MRSA §3110, sub-§2, as enacted by PL 2023, c. 412, Pt. VV, §1, is
32 amended to read:
33 2. Authorization required. Before providing any information pursuant to this
34 section, the department must receive express authorization from the recipient of assistance
