10 SUMMARY
1111 This amendment replaces the bill, which is a concept draft, and changes the title. The
1122 Department of Health and Human Services is developing an automatic referral process
1133 based on the provisions of Public Law 2023, chapter 412 to increase the number of
1144 individuals served by the department who are referred to, or enrolled in, other income
1155 supplementation and assistance programs. This amendment allows an individual to opt out
1166 of authorizing the release of specific information concerning the individual to facilitate that
1177 automatic referral or enrollment. The amendment also adds an emergency preamble and
1188 emergency clause.
